  "instructions": [
    "Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the grated ginger and minced garlic and cook for another minute.",
    "Add the chopped lemongrass, cinnamon, turmeric, salt, and black pepper, and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the chicken to the pot and cook until browned on all sides, about 5-7 minutes.",
    "Add the chicken broth and bring to a simmer.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 20-25 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through.",
    "Stir in the shredded parmesan cheese and blood orange juice.",
    "Taste and adjust the seasoning as needed.",
    "Serve the chicken hot, garnished with chopped fresh parsley."
